CatDescriptText: Mrs. Naomi Taylor, 22 Wooster Street, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 16, 1958, pg. 3 with question: "Do you think that Negroes are giving sufficient financial help to the National Association for the Advancement of Colored People?" answer reads: "I couldn't say yes or no, but there could be more given."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Naomi Taylor, wearing light colored sleeveless dress with polka dot and floral vertical stripes, eyeglasses with rhinestones, and light colored handbag with graphic pattern and scalloped edge, standing across from the Buhl Building, Fifth Avenue, Downtown
